PUT TOGETHER PHOTOS OF MY MOM

12:55.175 --> 12:58.178
FOR THE VIEWING, BUT I JUST
CAN'T LOOK AT THEM RIGHT NOW.

12:58.178 --> 13:00.213
I THINK I'LL, UH,
DROP BY THE CEMETERY

13:00.213 --> 13:02.715
TO SEE WHICH PLOT
I WANT TO GIVE HER.

13:02.715 --> 13:06.186
UH, OH, UM, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M GONNA WATCH SOME TV.

13:06.186 --> 13:08.188
YEAH, THERE'S A SPECIAL ON

13:08.188 --> 13:10.390
ABOUT THE WORLD'S
MOST HORRIBLE HUSBANDS.

13:10.390 --> 13:12.292
YEAH.

13:12.292 --> 13:14.261
THEY CHEAT,
AND THEY'RE ABUSIVE.

13:14.261 --> 13:17.831
IT KINDA MAKES A LITTLE LIE
SEEM LIKE NOTHING, HUH?

13:25.005 --> 13:26.874
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

13:26.874 --> 13:29.709
UH... OKAY, ANGIE,
YOU'RE HURTING,

13:29.709 --> 13:31.578
SO I'M JUST
GONNA TELL THE TRUTH.

13:31.578 --> 13:34.547
THE OWNERS OF THE CEMETERY
WERE IN DEBT,

13:34.547 --> 13:38.251
AND THEY HAD TO SELL SOME LAND
BACK TO THE CITY.

13:38.251 --> 13:40.087
THE BOTTOM LINE IS, UM...

13:40.087 --> 13:42.089
THAT OUR PLOTS
ARE NOW GONNA BE

13:42.089 --> 13:45.325
UNDER A SWIMMING POOL
FOR DEAF KIDS.

13:45.325 --> 13:48.896
WHAT? THAT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.

13:48.896 --> 13:50.330
ANGIE, THEY NEED
THEIR OWN POOLS

13:50.330 --> 13:53.033
BECAUSE THEIR MARCO POLO GAMES
TAKE FOREVER.

13:53.033 --> 13:56.403
THEY'RE LIKE THIS--
"MARCO"...

14:02.109 --> 14:07.114
YOU NEVER BOUGHT
THREE PLOTS, DID YOU?

14:07.114 --> 14:09.016
ANGIE, LET ME EXPLAIN--
DID YOU?

14:09.016 --> 14:11.318
NO. I FORGOT TO BUY
THE THIRD PLOT.

14:11.318 --> 14:13.987
WHERE ARE WE SUPPOSED
TO PUT MY MOTHER?

14:13.987 --> 14:15.788
ANGIE, LISTEN,
I WENT TO THE CEMETERY,

14:15.788 --> 14:18.491
AND THE CLOSEST SPOT THEY HAD
WAS TWO PEOPLE DOWN.

14:18.491 --> 14:20.193
THAT'S NOT NEXT TO ME.

14:20.193 --> 14:23.230
BUT IT'S NOT THAT FAR.
I MEAN, IT'S LIKE--IT'S LIKE

14:23.230 --> 14:25.232
FROM THE OVEN TO THE TABLE.

14:25.232 --> 14:29.302
JUST IMAGINE A NICE,
DEAD ARMENIAN COUPLE, ANGIE,

14:29.302 --> 14:31.738
RIGHT THERE
WHERE THE SINK IS.

14:31.738 --> 14:34.841
NO. YOU RUINED THIS.

14:34.841 --> 14:37.911
I SAID I WANTED HER
NEXT TO ME.

14:43.216 --> 14:46.153
WOW, SHE SEEMED REALLY MAD.

14:46.153 --> 14:47.720
OH, I'VE NEVER SEEN HER
THIS UPSET.

14:47.720 --> 14:51.358
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
BOTHERING HER ABOUT HER MOM.

14:51.358 --> 14:54.227
NO, LOOK, I KNOW ANGIE, MAN.
I REALLY SCREWED UP THIS TIME.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.229
THIS ONE'S ABOUT ME.
WELL, I'M JUST SAYING,

14:56.229 --> 14:58.531
A LOT OF TIMES
WHEN SOMEONE DIES SUDDENLY,

14:58.531 --> 15:01.234
ALL THE PEOPLE
CLOSE TO THEM ARE LEFT

15:01.234 --> 15:04.304
HOLDING A BAG
OF UNEXPRESSED EMOTIONS.

15:07.174 --> 15:10.777
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

15:10.777 --> 15:12.312
ALL RIGHT, CHECK IT OUT.

15:12.312 --> 15:14.281
WHEN MY AUNTCUCADIED,
MY MOM SEEMED OKAY

15:14.281 --> 15:16.283
UNTIL I ASKED HER
FOR SOME LEMONADE.

15:16.283 --> 15:18.952
THEN SHE STARTED BEATING ME
WITH A WOODEN SPOON.

15:18.952 --> 15:21.921
PALO,PALO,
BUT IT TURNS OUT,

15:21.921 --> 15:23.356
THAT WHEN
THEY WERE LITTLE GIRLS,

15:23.356 --> 15:26.326
THEY HAD A LEMONADE STAND,
AND MY MOM STOLE THE MONEY,

15:26.326 --> 15:28.828
SO WHEN MY AUNT DIED,
MY MOM FELT GUILTY

15:28.828 --> 15:31.331
BECAUSE
SHE NEVER TOLD HER.

15:31.331 --> 15:33.333
YOU MIGHT WANT TO ASK ANGIE

15:33.333 --> 15:36.803
IF SHE AND HER MOM
EVER HAD A LEMONADE STAND,

15:36.803 --> 15:40.273
OR A PAPER ROUTE OR...

15:40.273 --> 15:42.809
TÃºSABES, ANY OTHER KIND
OF SMALL BUSINESS ENDEAVOR

15:42.809 --> 15:46.246
THAT COULD'VE LED
TO AN UNRESOLVED GRIEVANCE.

15:48.415 --> 15:50.417
WHAT HAPPENED, MAN,
WHAT HAPPENED?

15:50.417 --> 15:53.820
YOU STARTED TALKING,
AND THEN I BLACKED OUT.

15:53.820 --> 15:55.288
"UNEXPRESSED EMOTION"?

15:55.288 --> 15:57.390
ESTÃ¡ LOCO,
"UNEXPRESSED EMOTION"!

16:03.296 --> 16:05.598
ANGIE...
I DON'T FEEL LIKE TALKING.

16:05.598 --> 16:07.634
LOOK, I'LL GO
TO A DIFFERENT CEMETERY

16:07.634 --> 16:09.269
WHERE WE CAN GET
THREE SPOTS TOGETHER.

16:09.269 --> 16:11.138
IT'S TOO LATE.
NO, IT'S NOT.

16:11.138 --> 16:13.140
LOOK, ANGIE, I'LL DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

16:13.140 --> 16:15.308
I MEAN,
I'LL BORROW THE MONEY,

16:15.308 --> 16:18.511
WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO GET THIS FIXED.
NO. DROP IT. IT DOESN'T MATTER.

16:18.511 --> 16:22.115
IT CAN'T BE FIXED.
IT CAN NEVER BE FIXED.

16:23.816 --> 16:25.618
LOOK, I--

16:25.618 --> 16:27.620
I'M JUST GONNA
GO AHEAD AND ASK.

16:27.620 --> 16:33.093
ANGIE, DID YOU AND YOUR MOM
EVER HAVE A... LEMONADE STAND?

16:33.093 --> 16:36.796
WHAT THE HELL
DOES THAT MEAN?

16:36.796 --> 16:39.499
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE YOU'RE NOT MAD AT ME.

16:39.499 --> 16:42.869
MAYBE YOU GOT A BAG
OF UNEXPRESSED EMOTIONS.

16:42.869 --> 16:45.838
I WISH
THEY WERE UNEXPRESSED.

16:45.838 --> 16:47.940
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I DID?

16:47.940 --> 16:50.510
WHEN WE WERE
ON THE PHONE LAST WEEK,

16:50.510 --> 16:54.381
I TOLD HER I NEVER FORGAVE HER
FOR CHEATING ON MY DAD.

16:54.381 --> 16:57.884
I CALLED HER A SELFISH TRAMP.

16:57.884 --> 17:00.687
THAT...

17:00.687 --> 17:04.091
IS THE LAST THING
I SAID TO MY MOTHER.

17:04.091 --> 17:07.294
OH, BABY,
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.
(sobs)

17:07.294 --> 17:10.029
COME ON. LOOK, SHE KNEW
YOU LOVED HER, ANGIE.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.031
ONE FIGHT
WOULDN'T CHANGE THAT.

17:12.031 --> 17:15.034
I CAN NEVER SAY I'M SORRY.

17:15.034 --> 17:17.937
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO MAKE THIS BETTER

17:17.937 --> 17:19.439
NOW THAT SHE'S GONE.

17:21.708 --> 17:25.278
WELL, I'M NOT GONNA LIE.
IT'S GONNA BE A LOT TOUGHER NOW.

17:25.278 --> 17:27.247
GEORGE.
OKAY, LOOK, ANGIE,

17:27.247 --> 17:30.750
DO YOU REMEMBER HOW MANY TIMES
CARMEN SAID "I HATE YOU" TO US?

17:30.750 --> 17:33.120
47 TIMES.

17:33.120 --> 17:34.121
YOU COUNTED?

17:34.121 --> 17:36.156
YEAH, IT HURT.

17:36.156 --> 17:38.158
OKAY, OKAY, IT HURT.

17:38.158 --> 17:40.460
BUT DID YOU EVER BELIEVE
FOR ONE MINUTE

17:40.460 --> 17:42.662
THAT--THAT CARMEN
DIDN'T LOVE YOU?

17:42.662 --> 17:44.597
NO.

17:44.597 --> 17:46.733
IT'S THE SAME THING
WITH YOUR MOM.

17:46.733 --> 17:50.137
IT'S ALL IN THAT BOOK SHE SENT
YOU AFTER SHE LEFT YOUR DAD.

17:50.137 --> 17:53.005
I WAS SO MAD AT HER,
I NEVER EVEN OPENED IT.

17:53.005 --> 17:54.174
I DID.

17:57.710 --> 18:02.315
WHY WOULD YOU READ A BOOK CALLED
"SINS OF THE MOTHER"?

18:02.315 --> 18:04.217
WELL, I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

18:04.217 --> 18:08.821
IT FELL OPEN AFTER I THREW IT
AT THAT SPIDER IN THE BATHROOM.

18:08.821 --> 18:12.091
YOU USED A BOOK MY MOM GAVE ME
TO KILL A SPIDER?

18:12.091 --> 18:13.760
KILL? I WISH.

18:13.760 --> 18:16.263
I JUST GOT TWO OF ITS LEGS,
ANGIE.

18:16.263 --> 18:18.265
IT'S STILL AROUND HERE
SOMEWHERE,

18:18.265 --> 18:20.567
TRAINING, GETTING STRONGER.

18:22.202 --> 18:24.704
SHE WROTE SOMETHING
IN THE FRONT FOR YOU.

18:28.308 --> 18:30.943
"I READ THIS AND I CRIED,

18:30.943 --> 18:35.782
"AND THEN I SMILED,
BECAUSE IT MADE ME THINK OF US.

18:35.782 --> 18:39.051
"I KNOW YOU MUST BE
ANGRY WITH ME,

18:39.051 --> 18:43.089
"BUT NO MATTER
WHAT HAPPENS,

18:43.089 --> 18:46.159
"I'M YOUR MOTHER,

18:46.159 --> 18:50.797
AND I WILL
ALWAYS LOVE YOU."

18:52.799 --> 18:57.136
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR SHOWING ME THIS.

18:57.136 --> 19:00.973
YOU FEEL BETTER?

19:00.973 --> 19:04.010
YEAH.

19:04.010 --> 19:05.345
I JUST...

19:05.345 --> 19:07.814
I JUST WISH
THERE WAS SOME WAY

19:07.814 --> 19:11.518
I COULD SHOW HER
HOW MUCH SHE MEANT TO ME.

19:11.518 --> 19:14.687
YOU COULD KEEP
HER MEMORY ALIVE.

19:14.687 --> 19:17.757
YOU KNOW, MAX WAS ASKING ME
ABOUT HER YESTERDAY.

19:17.757 --> 19:21.027
I COULD TELL HIM
ALL ABOUT HER LIFE.

19:21.027 --> 19:23.095
THERE YOU GO.

19:23.095 --> 19:25.665
SO...

19:25.665 --> 19:29.001
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT MY MOM?

19:29.001 --> 19:32.205
WELL, WHY DON'T WE GIVE
OUR SPOTS TO YOUR PARENTS,

19:32.205 --> 19:34.207
AND WHICHEVER
ONE OF US DIES FIRST

19:34.207 --> 19:36.609
GETS TAKEN CARE OF
BY THE OTHER?

19:36.609 --> 19:40.413
YOU'RE GONNA DUMP ME OFF
ON THE CITY, AREN'T YOU?

19:45.552 --> 19:49.289
ANGIE,
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

19:49.289 --> 19:52.659
"CAN YOU IDENTIFY THIS BODY,
SIR?"

19:52.659 --> 19:56.829
"I'M SORRY, I DON'T KNOW HER,
BUT SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

19:56.829 --> 19:58.931
BYE, ANGIE."

20:07.374 --> 20:09.342
HEY, WHAT'S THAT?

20:09.342 --> 20:11.811
IT'S A SCRAPBOOK
OF OLD PHOTOS OF MY MOM.

20:11.811 --> 20:15.648
I'M LEARNING
ABOUT GRANDMA'S LIFE.

20:19.886 --> 20:23.122
THIS IS GRANDMA EMELINA
IN THE FOURTH GRADE.

20:23.122 --> 20:25.825
HERE SHE IS UNDER A TREE...

20:25.825 --> 20:30.897
THIS IS GREAT. I FEEL LIKE
I REALLY KNOW HER.

20:34.233 --> 20:39.906
ANGIE, DIDN'T YOUR MOM
KEEP A DIARY?

20:39.906 --> 20:45.445
THAT'S RIGHT. SHE WROTE A PAGE
FOR EVERY DAY OF HER LIFE,

20:45.445 --> 20:48.881
STARTING
FROM WHEN SHE WAS 13.

20:48.881 --> 20:51.751
I HAVE IT UPSTAIRS.

21:00.593 --> 21:03.596
THANKS A LOT!
I SAID I FELT BAD.

21:03.596 --> 21:06.766
I DIDN'T SAY I WANTED
TO TAKE "GRANDMA 101."

21:08.100 --> 21:09.902
HEY, IT MAKES
YOUR MOM HAPPY,

21:09.902 --> 21:13.506
AND IT'S A NICE WAY
TO HONOR YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

21:13.506 --> 21:16.709
HEY, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
I'M-A GO PLAY GOLF.

21:16.709 --> 21:20.347
I'LL BE BACK IN FIVE HOURS.
YOU SHOULD BE DONE BY THEN.

21:20.347 --> 21:31.624
SEE YA LATER, SUCKER!
GOT YOU!
